def: A species of mint (Mentha viridis) growing in moist soil. Itvields an aromatic oil. See Mint, and Mentha.
One who, or that which, heals.
An intimate companion.Hail-fellow well met. Lyly.
To form into a hydrate; to combine with water.
An apothecium in certain lichens, having a spherical surfacemarked with spiral or concentric ridges and furrows.
A bushman carrying a swag and traveling on foot; -- called alsoswagsman, swagger, and swaggie.
Not having good repute; disreputable; disgraceful; inglorius.[R.] Shak.
Infectious particles or germs floating in the air; air madenoxious by the presence of such particles or germs; noxious effluvia;malaria.
